  "texts": [
    "(2) Alex is taller.",
    "(Implicit Comparative)",
    "(3) Kai bi Anna gao.",
    "Kai than Anna tall \"Kai is taller than Anna\" (Comparative in Mandarin Chinese)",
    "Crosslinguistically, the comparative form of a gradable adjective tall-er is either derived from or identical to its plain form (also called \"positive\" form) tall (Grano 2012; Grano and Davis 2018; Cong 2021)."
  ]
}